<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>3135</anchor> <rss>erct-001L.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001L</addr>  <route>erct-001L.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">Propositions</link> are <link href="erct-001J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001J" title="Sets">sets</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001L.agda" type="external">erct-001L.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If a type <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>, then it is a <link href="erct-001J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001J" title="Sets">set</link>.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>3136</anchor> <rss>erct-001E.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>erct-001E</addr>  <route>erct-001E.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The truncation hierarchy</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>1</crumb></trail> <anchor>3137</anchor> <rss>erct-001H.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001H</addr>  <route>erct-001H.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Contractibility</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001H.agda" type="external">erct-001H.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is said to be <em><strong>contractible with centre <tex>a:A</tex></strong></em> when every <tex>x:A</tex> is equipped with an identification <tex>\chi _x \colon  a = x</tex>. We say that <tex>A</tex> is <em><strong>contractible</strong></em> when it comes equipped with some <tex>a:A</tex> such that <tex>A</tex> is contractible with centre <tex>a</tex>. We sometimes refer to a contractible type as a <em><strong>singleton</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>2</crumb></trail> <anchor>3138</anchor> <rss>erct-001I.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001I</addr>  <route>erct-001I.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Propositions</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001I.agda" type="external">erct-001I.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is said to be a <em><strong>proposition</strong></em> when every <tex>x:A</tex>, the type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible with centre</link> <tex>x</tex>, i.e. all elements of <tex>A</tex> are identified.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>3</crumb></trail> <anchor>3139</anchor> <rss>erct-001J.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001J</addr>  <route>erct-001J.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Sets</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001J.agda" type="external">erct-001J.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is called a <em><strong>set</strong></em> when for each <tex>x,y:A</tex> the identification type <tex>x=y</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><p>The notions of <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible</link> and <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">propositional</link> types generate an infinite hierarchy of <em>truncation levels</em> expressing the point after which higher identifications become trivial.</p><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>4</crumb></trail> <anchor>3140</anchor> <rss>erct-001F.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Convention</taxon> <addr>erct-001F</addr>  <route>erct-001F.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Indexing of truncation levels</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001F.agda" type="external">erct-001F.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>truncation level</strong></em> is an integer <tex>n  \geq  -2</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>5</crumb></trail> <anchor>3141</anchor> <rss>erct-001G.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001G</addr>  <route>erct-001G.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><tex>n</tex>-truncated type</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001G.agda" type="external">erct-001G.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Given a <link href="erct-001F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001F" title="Indexing of truncation levels">truncation level</link> <tex>n</tex>, we define what it means for a type to be <em><strong><tex>n</tex>-truncated</strong></em> by induction:</p><ul><li>a type is <em><strong><tex>-2</tex>-truncated</strong></em> when it is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible</link>;</li>
  <li>a type is <em><strong><tex>-1</tex>-truncated</strong></em> when it is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>;</li>
  <li>for <tex>n  \geq  0</tex>, a type <tex>A</tex> is <em><strong><tex>n</tex>-truncated</strong></em> when for every <tex>x,y:A</tex> the identification type <tex>x=y</tex> is <tex>n-1</tex>-truncated.</li></ul><p>So, in particular, a <tex>0</tex>-truncated type is precisely a <em>set</em>. We shall often refer to <tex>n</tex>-truncated types as <em><strong><tex>n</tex>-types</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>6</crumb></trail> <anchor>3142</anchor> <rss>erct-001T.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001T</addr>  <route>erct-001T.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><tex>n</tex>-truncated map</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001T.agda" type="external">erct-001T.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is called <em><strong><tex>n</tex>-truncated</strong></em> when all of its <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fibers</link> are <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><tex>n</tex>-truncated types</link>. By analogy, we shall also refer to maps as <em><strong>contractible</strong></em> when their fibers are; we shall refer to maps as <em><strong>embeddings</strong></em> when their fibers are <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">propositions</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>7</crumb></trail> <anchor>3143</anchor> <rss>erct-001K.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001K</addr>  <route>erct-001K.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">Contractible</link> types are <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">propositions</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001K.agda" type="external">erct-001K.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If a type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible</link>, then it is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
  As <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible</link> with some centre <tex>a:A</tex>, we have for any <tex>x,y:A</tex> identifications <tex>\chi _x  \colon  a = x</tex> and <tex>\chi _y \colon  a = y</tex>. Therefore, we identify <tex>x</tex> with <tex>y</tex> using <tex>\chi _x ^{-1}   \cdot   \chi _y</tex>.
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>9</crumb></trail> <anchor>3144</anchor> <rss>erct-002T.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002T</addr>  <route>erct-002T.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type">Truncation</link> is upward closed</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002T.agda" type="external">erct-002T.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If a type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</link>, then it is also <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 We proceed by induction on the <link href="erct-001F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001F" title="Indexing of truncation levels">truncation level</link> <tex>n</tex>, with two base cases:
 <ul><li>If <tex>n=-2</tex>, we recall that <link href="erct-001K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001K" title="Contractible types are propositions">contractible types are propositions</link>.</li>
  <li>If <tex>n=-1</tex>, we recall that <link href="erct-001L.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001L" title="Propositions are sets">propositions are sets</link>.</li></ul>
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>10</crumb></trail> <anchor>3145</anchor> <rss>erct-002U.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002U</addr>  <route>erct-002U.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The identity map is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002U.agda" type="external">erct-002U.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>For any type <tex>A</tex>, the identity map <tex>1_{ A } \colon  A \to  A</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> Immediate by identification induction.</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>11</crumb></trail> <anchor>3146</anchor> <rss>erct-002V.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-002V</addr>  <route>erct-002V.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The identity map is <tex>n</tex>-truncated for all <tex>n</tex></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002V.agda" type="external">erct-002V.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>For any type <tex>A</tex>, the identity map <tex>1_{ A } \colon  A \to  A</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</link> for all <tex>n</tex>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 We proceed by induction on the <link href="erct-001F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001F" title="Indexing of truncation levels">truncation level</link> <tex>n</tex>: when <tex>n=-2</tex>, we recall that the <link href="erct-002U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002U" title="The identity map is contractible">identity map is contractible</link>, and in the inductive step we apply the <link href="erct-002T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002T" title="Truncation is upward closed">upward closure of <tex>n</tex>-truncation</link> to each <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>1_{ A }</tex>.
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>12</crumb></trail> <anchor>3147</anchor> <rss>erct-0026.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-0026</addr>  <route>erct-0026.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">Propositions</link> are closed under <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retracts</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0026.agda" type="external">erct-0026.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>B</tex> and <tex>B</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>, then <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 This can be seen using the cancellation laws of retractions.
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>13</crumb></trail> <anchor>3148</anchor> <rss>erct-0027.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-0027</addr>  <route>erct-0027.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">Contractible</link> types are closed under <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retracts</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0027.agda" type="external">erct-0027.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>B</tex> and <tex>B</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible</link>, then <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 Let <tex>s \colon  A  \to  B</tex> be a section of <tex>r \colon  B \to  A</tex>; if <tex>b_0</tex> is the centre of contraction of <tex>B</tex>, then the centre of contraction of <tex>A</tex> is given by <tex>rb_0</tex>. For the rest, we use the fact that <link href="erct-0026.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0026" title="Propositions are closed under retracts">propositions are closed under retracts</link> and <link href="erct-001K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001K" title="Contractible types are propositions">contractible types are propositions</link>.
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>14</crumb></trail> <anchor>3149</anchor> <rss>erct-0028.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Axiom</taxon> <addr>erct-0028</addr>  <route>erct-0028.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Propositional truncation</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0028.agda" type="external">erct-0028.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>For any type <tex>A</tex> we have a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link> <tex>\mathsf {toProp} \, {A}</tex> equipped with a unit map <tex>\eta _{ \mathsf {prop}} \colon  A  \to \mathsf {toProp} \, {A}</tex>; moreover, we have the following induction principle: for any family of <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">propositions</link> <tex>B \colon   \mathsf {toProp} \, A  \to   \mathsf {Prop}</tex>, any function <tex>b \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }  B \mathopen {} \left ( \eta _{ \mathsf {prop}} \, x \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> extends to a function <tex>b^ \sharp   \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }  Bx</tex>.</p><p>When we have an element of <tex>\mathsf {toProp} \, A</tex>, we will say that <tex>A</tex> is <em><strong>inhabited</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>15</crumb></trail> <anchor>3150</anchor> <rss>erct-002A.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-002A</addr>  <route>erct-002A.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Inhabitation and existence</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is called <em><strong>inhabited</strong></em> when we have an element of <tex>\mathsf {toProp} \, A</tex>. When we say <em><strong>there exists</strong></em>, we refer to inhabitation.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>16</crumb></trail> <anchor>3151</anchor> <rss>erct-0029.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0029</addr>  <route>erct-0029.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Surjection</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is called <em><strong>surjective</strong></em> when for any <tex>b \colon  B</tex>, the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>b</tex> is <link href="erct-002A.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002A" title="Inhabitation and existence">inhabited</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>3152</anchor> <rss>erct-001I.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001I</addr>  <route>erct-001I.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Propositions</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001I.agda" type="external">erct-001I.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is said to be a <em><strong>proposition</strong></em> when every <tex>x:A</tex>, the type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible with centre</link> <tex>x</tex>, i.e. all elements of <tex>A</tex> are identified.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>3153</anchor> <rss>erct-001J.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001J</addr>  <route>erct-001J.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Sets</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001J.agda" type="external">erct-001J.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is called a <em><strong>set</strong></em> when for each <tex>x,y:A</tex> the identification type <tex>x=y</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>3154</anchor> <rss>erct-002T.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002T</addr>  <route>erct-002T.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type">Truncation</link> is upward closed</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002T.agda" type="external">erct-002T.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If a type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</link>, then it is also <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 We proceed by induction on the <link href="erct-001F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001F" title="Indexing of truncation levels">truncation level</link> <tex>n</tex>, with two base cases:
 <ul><li>If <tex>n=-2</tex>, we recall that <link href="erct-001K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001K" title="Contractible types are propositions">contractible types are propositions</link>.</li>
  <li>If <tex>n=-1</tex>, we recall that <link href="erct-001L.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001L" title="Propositions are sets">propositions are sets</link>.</li></ul>
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>3155</anchor> <rss>erct-001N.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001N</addr>  <route>erct-001N.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001N.agda" type="external">erct-001N.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>It is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link> that a given type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
  <p>Suppose we have two centres of contraction <tex>a,a':A</tex> with <tex>\chi _ \bullet \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } a = x</tex> and <tex>\chi '_ \bullet \colon \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } a'=x</tex> as witnesses of contraction. To identify <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( a, \chi _ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> with <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( a', \chi '_ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>, we employ the <link href="erct-0035.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0035" title="Covariant sum of an opfibrant family of univalent reflexive graphs">covariant sum</link> of each of the <link href="erct-001C.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001C" title="Dependent product of univalent reflexive graphs">pointwise univalent reflexive graph</link> structures on <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } -=x</tex> over the <link href="erct-0013.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0013" title="The intrinsic univalent reflexive graph">intrinsic univalent reflexive graph</link> structure on <tex>A</tex>, constructing an identification <tex>p \colon  a = a'</tex> followed by a homotopy <tex>H  \colon   \mathopen {} \left ( \mathopen {} \left ( \chi _{a'} \right ) \mathclose {} _*^{ \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } -=x}  \chi _ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}   \sim   \chi '_ \bullet</tex>. Fixing <tex>z \colon  A</tex>, we compute:</p>

  <tex display="block">
     \begin {aligned}
       \mathopen {} \left ( \mathopen {} \left ( \chi _{a'} \right ) \mathclose {} _*^{ \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } -=x}  \chi _ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}  z
      &amp;=
       \mathopen {} \left ( \chi _{a'} \right ) \mathclose {} _*^{-=z}  \chi _z
       \\ 
      &amp;=
       \chi _{a'} ^{-1}   \cdot   \chi _z
       \\ 
      &amp;=  \chi '_z
     \end {aligned}
  </tex>

  <p>The first and second steps follow from general computation lemmas for transport, and the last step follows from the fact that <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001J" title="Sets">set</link>, which we may deduce as <link href="erct-001K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001K" title="Contractible types are propositions">contractible types are propositions</link> and <link href="erct-001L.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001L" title="Propositions are sets">propositions are sets</link>.</p>
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>3156</anchor> <rss>erct-001O.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001O</addr>  <route>erct-001O.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001O.agda" type="external">erct-001O.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>It is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link> that a given type <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
  To identify two witnesses <tex>\phi , \phi '  \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } x = y</tex> that <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>, it suffices via the <link href="erct-0015.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0015" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions">pointwise univalent univalence principle for functions</link> to exhibit a double homotopy in <tex>A</tex> identifying each <tex>\phi  xy</tex> with <tex>\phi 'xy</tex>. As <link href="erct-001L.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001L" title="Propositions are sets">propositions are sets</link>, this follows from our assumption that <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>.
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>